p10
aVafter they were born.
p11
aVAnd I was sitting there and saying,
p12
aV"This is where my tax dollars are wasted \u2014
p13
aa(lp14
V(Laughter)
p15
aa(lp16
Von this kind of soft science."
p17
aa(lp18
VAnd he started telling me
p19
aVthat the rats, like humans,
p20
aVlick their pups in very different ways.
p21
aVSome mothers do a lot of that,
p22
aVsome mothers do very little,
p23
aVand most are in between.
p24
aVBut what's interesting about it
p25
aVis when he follows these pups when they become adults \u2014
p26
aVlike, years in human life, long after their mother died.
p27
aVThey are completely different animals.
p28
aVThe animals that were licked and groomed heavily,
p29
aVthe high-licking and grooming,
p30
aVare not stressed.
p31
aVThey have different sexual behavior.
