aa(lp229
VSo if we can program genes,
p230
aVif we are not just the slaves of the history of our genes,
p231
aVthat they could be programmed, can we deprogram them?
p232
aVBecause epigenetic causes can cause diseases like cancer,
p233
aVmetabolic disease
p234
aVand mental health diseases.
p235
aa(lp236
VLet's talk about cocaine addiction.
p237
aVCocaine addiction is a terrible situation
p238
aVthat can lead to death and to loss of human life.
p239
aVWe asked the question:
p240
aVCan we reprogram the addicted brain
p241
aVto make that animal not addicted anymore?
p242
aVWe used a cocaine addiction model
p243
aVthat recapitulates what happens in humans.
p244
aVIn humans, you're in high school,
p245
aVsome friends suggest you use some cocaine,
p246
aVyou take cocaine, nothing happens.
p247
aVMonths pass by, something reminds you of what happened the first time,
p248
aVa pusher pushes cocaine,
p249
aVand you become addicted and your life has changed.
p250
aa(lp251
VIn rats, we do the same thing.
p252
aVMy colleague, Gal Yadid,
p253
aVhe trains the animals to get used to cocaine,
p254
aVthen for one month, no cocaine.
p255
aVThen he reminds them of the party when they saw the cocaine the first time
p256
aVby cue, the colors of the cage when they saw cocaine.
p257
aVAnd they go crazy.
p258
aVThey will press the lever to get cocaine
p259
aVuntil they die.
p260
aVWe first determined that the difference between these animals
p261
aVis that during that time when nothing happens,
p262
aVthere's no cocaine around,
p263
aVtheir epigenome is rearranged.
p264
aVTheir genes are re-marked in a different way,
p265
aVand when the cue comes, their genome is ready
p266
aVto develop this addictive phenotype.
p267
aa(lp268
VSo we treated these animals with drugs that either increase DNA methylation,
p269
aVwhich was the epigenetic marker to look at,
p270
aVor decrease epigenetic markings.
p271
aVAnd we found that if we increased methylation,
p272
aVthese animals go even crazier.
p273
aVThey become more craving for cocaine.
p274
aVBut if we reduce the DNA methylation,
p275
aVthe animals are not addicted anymore.
p276
aVWe have reprogrammed them.
p277
aVAnd a fundamental difference between an epigenetic drug
p278
aVand any other drug
p279
aVis that with epigenetic drugs,
p280
aVwe essentially remove the signs of experience,
p281
aVand once they're gone,
p282
aVthey will not come back unless you have the same experience.
p283
aVThe animal now is reprogrammed.
p284
aVSo when we visited the animals 30 days, 60 days later,
p285
aVwhich is in human terms many years of life,
p286
aVthey were still not addicted \u2014 by a single epigenetic treatment.
p287
aa(lp288
VSo what did we learn about DNA?
p289
aVDNA is not just a sequence of letters;
p290
aVit's not just a script.
p291
aVDNA is a dynamic movie.
p292
aVOur experiences are being written into this movie, which is interactive.
p293
aVYou're, like, watching a movie of your life, with the DNA,
p294
aVwith your remote control.
p295
aVYou can remove an actor and add an actor.
p296
aVAnd so you have, in spite of the deterministic nature of genetics,
p297
aVyou have control of the way your genes look,
p298
aVand this has a tremendous optimistic message
p299
aVfor the ability to now encounter some of the deadly diseases
p300
aVlike cancer, mental health,
p301
aVwith a new approach,
p302
aVlooking at them as maladaptation.
p303
aVAnd if we can epigenetically intervene,
p304
aV[we can] reverse the movie by removing an actor
p305
aVand setting up a new narrative.
p306
aa(lp307
VSo what I told you today is,
p308
aVour DNA is really combined of two components,
p309
aVtwo layers of information.
p310
aVOne layer of information is old,
p311
aVevolved from millions of years of evolution.
p312
aVIt is fixed and very hard to change.
p313
aVThe other layer of information is the epigenetic layer,
p314
aVwhich is open and dynamic
p315
aVand sets up a narrative that is interactive,
p316
aVthat allows us to control, to a large extent, our destiny,
p317
aVto help the destiny of our children
p318
aVand to hopefully conquer disease
p319
aVand serious health challenges
p320
aVthat have plagued humankind for a long time.
p321
aa(lp322
VSo even though we are determined
p323
aVby our genes,
p324
aVwe have a degree of freedom
p325
aVthat can set up our life to a life of responsibility.
